The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has approved Saturday, Feb. 19, for the conclusion of its outstanding State Congress for the purpose of electing new State Executive Committee members in Lagos State The party disclosed this in a statement issued by its National Organising Secretary, Umar Bature, on Thursday in Abuja. The NW, according to the statement, also scheduled a crucial meeting with Lagos State stakeholders on Monday, Feb. 7, at the Zonal Headquarters, Ibadan, Oyo State. It added that the NWC would continue to update stakeholders on any development in that regard. By Chimezie Anaso   The leadership crisis in the Anambra chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) was thought to have been resolved after the state’s congress at the party headquarters in Awka on Dec.4, 2017. The congress was organised by the erstwhile Sen. Ahmed Makarfi-led interim National Caretaker Committee… In "Politics" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - Bayelsa State Gover­nor, Henry Seriake Dickson, has called on all leaders of the Peop­les Democratic Party (PDP) to support the Prince Uche Seco­ndus - led National Working Working Comm­ittee (NWC) of the party to deliver on its mandate. The governor said it is by so doing… In "Politics" The National Working Committee (NWC) of the PDP has extended the deadline for submission of already completed nomination forms for state congresses from the earlier announced date of Sept. 23 to Oct. 1. The party in a statement issued by its PDP National Publicity, Mr Kola Ologbondiyan, in Abuja on… In "Politics"